1006.m_mText: "'This is my family's domain,' Empousa declared imperiously. 'As a guest, shouldn't you show some respect to your hosts?'"

1007.m_mText: "'Your family's domain?' Hati scoffed, her anger barely contained. 'Fangtooth Tower belongs to the Ganelon family.'"

1008.m_mText: "'All the land on the Howling Peninsula was forcibly occupied by your family,' Empousa shouted, hands on her hips. 'I've told you to read more, you dim-witted wolf!'"

1009.m_mText: "Hati's anger flared up. 'For as long as I can remember, this place has belonged to the Ganelon family!'"

1010.m_mText: "'How many years can your puny memory even span, you dumb wolf!' Empousa exclaimed, exasperated by the futility of reasoning with her."

1011.m_mText: "'Oh come on, what are you two bickering about now?' Jestel called out as she made her way up to join them. 'Empousa, weren't we supposed to be here to enjoy the sea view?'"

1012.m_mText: "'Besides, the Ganelon family is no longer...' Jestel's words trailed off as realization dawned. Even with her usual lack of tact, she understood too late that this might wound Hati."

1014.m_mText: "'It's fine,' Hati muttered, averting her gaze."

1015.m_mText: "Facing the sea breeze at the tower's edge, Hati said, 'I've heard the Bathorys plan to station troops here. They're preparing for a potential sea assault on the castle by the Church from the east.'"

1016.m_mText: "'Yes, I've heard that too,' Empousa nodded. 'But unlike you, we can't control the wolf packs in Lupine Forest. This tower can only function as an early warning system at best.'"

1017.m_mText: "Empousa and Jestel joined Hati at the edge. Together, the three stood silently, letting the salty sea breeze caress their faces as they watched the waves crash rhythmically against the distant shore."

1018.m_mText: "'Hey Hati, I've heard the sunset here is beautiful. Is it true?' Empousa asked."

1019.m_mText: "Hati said with a bitter smile, 'I've heard about it too. Having lived on the land my whole life, I'm curious about a sunset over the sea.'"

1020.m_mText: "'In fact, the tower is mentioned countless times in the castle's archives and various historical records. It has been destroyed at least thirteen times throughout its history.'"

1021.m_mText: "'Wow, I had no idea the tower had such an incredible history!' Hati exclaimed, her eyes wide with amazement."

1022.m_mText: "'You didn't actually understand a word I said, did you?' Empousa asked sarcastically, shooting Hati a withering look."

1023.m_mText: "'Heh heh,' Hati chuckled nervously, her discomfort evident."

1024.m_mText: "'Moreover, it played a crucial role in a certain campaign,' Empousa added, her eyes gleaming with barely concealed pride."

1025.m_mText: "'Oh, you mean the Battle of the Lone Tower?' Jestel suddenly chimed in."

1026.m_mText: "'You know about it too!' Empousa exclaimed, her face lighting up with delight."

1027.m_mText: "'Well, of course. The Aegis family took part in that battle too. But it's not really something to be proud of, is it?'"

1028.m_mText: "'What do you mean it's not?' Empousa put her hands on her hips. 'We Bathorys successfully repelled the enemy, thanks to the intel we got from Fangtooth Tower!'"

1029.m_mText: "'Would you like to hear how the Aegis family remembers that battle?'"

1030.m_mText: "'In the stories passed down through generations in the Aegis family, the Church was merely using the Ganelon family as pawns to trap the Bathory family on The Howling Peninsula.'"

1031.m_mText: "'Surprisingly, when the Ganelon lands faced a food crisis some time later, it was the Bathorys who came to their aid.'"

1032.m_mText: "'The two families were locked in a fierce rivalry on this peninsula for hundreds of years, until one day, a Ganelon betrayed the family.'"

1033.m_mText: "'That's impossible!' Hati cried out. 'The Ganelons are the epitome of loyalty!'"

1034.m_mText: "'I don't know the exact details, but I would guess he received the Embrace and became a Bloodborn. After that, this Ganelon helped the Bathory family launch a surprise attack on Mouret.'"

1035.m_mText: "'Some people fled to the Fangtooth Tower, planning to sail to the new continent. But the Enemy arrived so quickly that they were forced to take refuge in the tower.'"

1036.m_mText: "'The Aegis warriors hid behind massive shields, waiting for nightfall. They were determined to prevent anyone from escaping the tower.'"

1037.m_mText: "'The Ganelons in the tower began firing arrows. Anyone who charged the entrance was either shot dead or cut down by a Ganelon defender at the doorway.'"

1038.m_mText: "'Later, the attackers tried setting fires at the base of the tower, but even this failed to drive out the stalwart Ganelon defenders.'"

2001001.m_mText: "'Tell us! Tell us!' Hati suddenly leaned in, then realized this matter wasn't as glorious as Empousa had made it out to be."

2001002.m_mText: "'On second thought, forget it,' Empousa said, waving her hand dismissively. 'I couldn't care less about all that war stuff anyway.'"

2001003.m_mText: "Jestel let out a heavy sigh. 'But the Ganelon family is no more. We can't allow that chapter of history to simply fade into oblivion.'"

2002001.m_mText: "'On second thought, forget it,' Empousa said, waving her hand dismissively. 'I couldn't care less about all that war stuff anyway.'"

2002002.m_mText: "'Tell us! Tell us!' Hati suddenly leaned in, then realized this matter wasn't as glorious as Empousa had made it out to be."

2002003.m_mText: "Jestel let out a heavy sigh. 'But the Ganelon family is no more. We can't allow that chapter of history to simply fade into oblivion.'"

2003001.m_mText: "Empousa pulled Jestel aside: 'Hey, can you let me in on the secret?'"

2003002.m_mText: "Jestel glanced at Hati, her voice tinged with sorrow: 'The Ganelon family... they're gone...'"

2003003.m_mText: "The sparkle faded from Empousa's eyes. 'Fine, then spill the beans to both of us.'"

1.m_mText: "In her quest for botanical wisdom, Edina once journeyed alongside Yggdrasill, their travels weaving a tapestry of knowledge across the entire continent."

1002.m_mText: "As they traveled northward from the Eye of God, they planned to stop at Snowmelt Station upon approaching the vast snowy plains."

1003.m_mText: "Edina cupped her hands, sheltering and warming the delicate creature within, while scanning the snow-blanketed slopes for suitable plants."

1004.m_mText: "Edina's master approached her and, without looking, sensed that she was cradling protectively a butterfly with damaged wings in her hands."

1005.m_mText: "'Master, this butterfly just emerged from its cocoon, but its wings are damaged. I'm looking for plants that can heal it.'"

1006.m_mText: "'The life force a plant can absorb from the frozen earth is limited. Even restoring the life of a butterfly's could cost a shrub its life.'"

1007.m_mText: "'Then I'll find a big tree!' Edina exclaimed. Her hands trembled, the realization of her near mistake hitting her suddenly."

1008.m_mText: "'Be careful not to startle the little one in your hands,' Yggdrasill said, his words reflecting the boundless patience he had for his pupil."

1009.m_mText: "'Master, could you please heal it?' Edina asked hopefully, gently raising the butterfly towards Yggdrasill."

1010.m_mText: "'Why do you insist on saving it?' The Master's eyes remained utterly devoid of emotion."

1011.m_mText: "'Because it has just unfurled its wings, yet hasn't savored the joy of free flight. Its life is so fleeting...' Edina replied, a tinge of sorrow in her voice."

1012.m_mText: "'You perceive it as fleeting because you're measuring an insect's life by human standards,' Yggdrasill said, his gaze already fixed northward."

1013.m_mText: "'Even if we heal it, it cannot escape this snowy plain. The outcome of death is unchangeable.'"

1014.m_mText: "'The momentary warmth you offer it—is it truly poison or antidote? Can you really discern the difference?' With these words, Yggdrasill took long strides towards the house."

1015.m_mText: "Edina paused briefly, tenderly cradling the butterfly, then hastened to catch up with her master."

1016.m_mText: "'Master, have you heard the tale of the one who built this waystation?' Edina inquired after lighting the furnace."

1017.m_mText: "'I have no interest in human affairs,' Yggdrasill stated flatly. If not for his disciple, he wouldn't have set foot in this waystation at all."

1018.m_mText: "'Would you permit me to share his story with you?' Edina asked, sitting upright in her chair, hands folded neatly on her lap."

1019.m_mText: "'If you wish.' Yggdrasill thought he may as well consider it a simple bedtime story to pass the time."

1020.m_mText: "Legend tells that long ago, these snowy plains were even colder than they are now. Travelers heading north often froze to death before reaching Iron City. No ordinary person could endure such bitter cold."

1021.m_mText: "'Humans will always do what is necessary for survival, even if those very actions might lead to their demise.'"

1022.m_mText: "'As for the one who built this waystation, his tale begins simply enough—someone offered him a fortune to construct this refuge.'"

1023.m_mText: "'Initially, the foreman harbored no lofty ideals; he simply needed the money and had no choice but to accept this job.'"

1024.m_mText: "'His first headache was recruiting manpower. He quickly discovered that no one was willing to brave certain death on the snowy plains.'"

1025.m_mText: "'Should he fail to construct the waystation, he faces ruinous debts and even imprisonment. In such dire straits, what path would humans choose?'"

1026.m_mText: "Yggdrasill's branches and leaves stirred gently, as if contemplating the question with profound consideration."

1027.m_mText: "'He lay in wait outside the prison gates for days, finally finding a few recently released inmates with nowhere else to turn.'"

1028.m_mText: "'Is this pitiful grass huddling together for warmth, or a deception woven by oleanders blooming in a parched riverbed?'"

1029.m_mText: "At that time, Edina was still in her youth. The vast tapestry of the world had yet to unfurl before her eyes. The two possibilities her master described sometimes converged from the same horizon."

1030.m_mText: "Finally, Edina, after being interrupted several times, couldn't help but blurt out in a childish tone, 'Master, do you even want to hear this story anymore?'"

1031.m_mText: "Poor Yggdrasill resorted to fanning his disciple with his branches, hoping to cool down her flaring temper."

1032.m_mText: "'With that settled, the group set out for the pre-selected site, carrying enough supplies and materials to build the waystation.'"

1033.m_mText: "'But just as they began their journey, they were struck by a massive blizzard. Suddenly, they faced a grim reality: pressing on meant almost certain death for everyone in those merciless snowy plains.'"

2001001.m_mText: "'Might he have chosen flight? And yet, the outcome reveals that this human did not succumb to the temptation of escape.'"

2001002.m_mText: "'It's quite possible he did consider it. According to records left by his descendants, on the eve of departure, he spent the entire night in deep contemplation, gazing at the snowfall in the north. Ultimately, he chose not to abandon everything and leave.'"

2001003.m_mText: "'That is indeed intriguing. How did they eventually manage to find people to construct this waystation?'"

2002001.m_mText: "'Most people in this world are cunning. I wonder, did he perhaps conceal certain truths when recruiting workers?'"

2002002.m_mText: "'While evil does exist in this world, I firmly believe that the majority are good at heart. Just like plants... some are poisonous while others can cure ailments.'"

2002003.m_mText: "'But plants do not deceive. In this vast snowy expanse, lies will inevitably be scattered by the relentless winds.'"

2003001.m_mText: "'Master, do you smell something strange? Like something's burning...'"

2003002.m_mText: "Edina glanced around, then carefully opened her hands to ensure the butterfly was still safe."

2003003.m_mText: "'Hmm, perhaps this is the smell of philosophical contemplation...'"

2003004.m_mText: "Yggdrasill seemed to exhibit a bashful demeanor. Who'd have thought one could see such an emotion from a tree?"

2003005.m_mText: "As the story continued, Yggdrasill pulled his branches inward while shifting to curiosity as he inquired about the rest of the tale."

1.m_mText: "The ashen sky was blanketed with vast swaths of leaden clouds, hanging heavy like water-logged, tattered cotton. Below, their oppressive weight bore down upon a desolate fishing village."

1002.m_mText: "Through the thin mist, four men stood in a tense standoff in the village square. The sticky sea breeze tugged at their clothes and hair, yet failed to quench the fire burning in their eyes."

1003.m_mText: "Suddenly, the breeze fell silent. In that split second, one man seized his moment to act!"

1004.m_mText: "In a flash, he whipped out an object. A burst of dazzling golden light erupted from his palm. Everyone squinted, eyeing it warily. The tension was thick in the air."

1005.m_mText: "'Not that thing...' One voice called out anxiously, clearly wary of the golden glow."

1006.m_mText: "'Oh? So this is...' Another elegant voice chimed in, barely concealing their curiosity and excitement."

1007.m_mText: "As the thin mist dissipated, the the object was revealed—a golden hourglass. What set this timepiece apart, however, was the intricate carving of a man upon its surface."

1008.m_mText: "Interestingly, judging by its weight, that sculpture was clearly hollow and merely gold-plated... The reasoning behind this peculiar design? Well... that's another sad story altogether."

1009.m_mText: "The lifelike figure stood proudly atop the hourglass. His head was held high, arms spread wide in a pose of extravagant narcissism. As one's gaze lingered, the identity of this ostentatious figure became clear—it was none other than—"

1010.m_mText: "'—the one and only Kristoph Goldland!' Admiring the masterpiece in his palm, Goldland declared with unbridled enthusiasm, 'For us merchants, time is not merely precious—it is the very essence of gold itself!'"

1011.m_mText: "'Now, let the spectacle commence!' With a flourish, Goldland inverted the hourglass and set it on the ground. His voice rang out with theatrical grandeur, 'I hereby declare the greatest fishing competition in all of Minexus—'"

1012.m_mText: "The proclamation died on Goldland's lips as a sudden realization struck him. He fell into an abrupt silence, his brow furrowing deeply as he fixed an intense gaze upon the hourglass now resting on the ground."

1013.m_mText: "Ignoring the chatter of the other three, Goldland plonked himself down right where he stood. 'My magnificent golden body is upside down like a topsy-turvy turnip! This is absolutely, positively not beautiful! I simply cannot tolerate such an affront to aesthetics!'"

1014.m_mText: "'Eureka!' Goldland exclaimed, clapping his hands with unbridled excitement. 'We'll wait for this round of exquisite golden sand to finish its journey, then I'll flip it right side up, and we can commence our grand competition!'"

1015.m_mText: "'Did you really not consider the upside-down problem when designing this?' Noah stared in disbelief, though he quickly realized this was perfectly on-brand for Goldland."

1016.m_mText: "'Very well, let's use this interlude to clarify the competition rules,' Van Helsing glanced around. 'The competition will be team-based. The objective is simple: the team that catches the most fish within the time limit wins.'"

1017.m_mText: "'As we agreed earlier, I'm with Goldland, while you, Silver-haired, are paired with Cain. Hmph, remember, you chose this pairing yourself, Silver-haired! So don't come fishing for excuses if you end up on the losing side!'"

1018.m_mText: "After an eternity of anticipation, the last grain of sand finally trickled through. The (ostensibly) 'solid gold' (but secretly hollow) Statue of Goldland triumphantly flipped over and stood erect, its arms outstretched as if to embrace the heavens!"

1019.m_mText: "'Splendid! Now everything is truly, impeccably ready.' Goldland reverently placed the golden hourglass on the ground and, with a grandiose flourish, once again proclaimed, 'The Greatest Fishing Competition in All of Minexus—'"

1020.m_mText: "'Begins now!' The words had barely left his mouth before Goldland took off like a shot, his boisterous laughter echoing behind him. 'Ha ha ha ha! Van Helsing, stop them!'"

1021.m_mText: "'Huh? What's...' Noah stared puzzled in Goldland's direction."

1022.m_mText: "Van Helsing took up a fighting stance, eyeing the pair before him. 'My apologies, but I must keep you two here.'"

1024.m_mText: "'Goldland has done his research and found the best fishing spot in advance. As long as no one interferes with him, victory will be ours.'"

1026.m_mText: "'That's the essence of teamwork. He fishes while I block. Using the rules to our advantage is part of the game. Blame your lack of competition experience!'"

1028.m_mText: "'Hah, I know what you're thinking: that I alone can't defeat both of you.' Van Helsing said, all the while scanning his two opponents, watching for any sudden moves to pursue Goldland."

1029.m_mText: "'But I only need to hold you off until time runs out for our team to win!' Van Helsing looked down at the two opponents with pride. 'Strategy is just as much a part of strength as anything else.'"

1030.m_mText: "A ray of sunlight broke through the clouds and mist, enveloping Van Helsing in a golden glow. In this moment, he stood as the veritable incarnation of wisdom and strategy."

1031.m_mText: "'I think what Noah's been trying to say is that Goldland forgot his fishing rod,' Cain said, with a half-smirk at Van Helsing as he casually pointed to the ground nearby."

1032.m_mText: "A golden fishing rod lay conspicuously on the ground—its tip adorned with an engraving of an excessively flamboyant man, head held high and arms outstretched. The identity of its owner was painfully obvious."

1033.m_mText: "Van Helsing lapsed into silence. After a moment, he picked up the golden fishing rod and walked away, but not before leaving them with one last declaration: 'Never underestimate a man's determination!'"

1034.m_mText: "Seemingly touched by Van Helsing's unwavering spirit, Noah gazed in awe at his figure disappearing into the mist. It took him a long moment to shake off his daze. '...Didn't he go in the wrong direction?' he asked, bemused."

1035.m_mText: "Cain picked up the golden hourglass from the ground and, for some reason, began casually recounting Goldland's rise to power. 'As we all know, Goldland's business empire started with high-quality seafood at bargain prices.'"

1036.m_mText: "'Why, you ask, did he have access to so much seafood? The answer is simple: smuggling, of course!'"

1037.m_mText: "Noah froze at this shocking revelation—'Smuggling seafood?'"

1038.m_mText: "'Exactly! Goldland amassed enormous profits through seafood smuggling, throwing the entire Minexus seafood market into chaos. Every family on the continent has reached their breaking point with him.'"

1039.m_mText: "'This matter eventually caught the Church's attention, prompting them to issue their highest-level investigation order against him. They're using the Blood Beast investigation as a cover, while their real intention is to secretly take over Goldland's seafood empire.'"

1040.m_mText: "Noah felt a chill down his spine. He and Ami had once profited from selling overpriced seafood to Friedrich... Could this be the real reason the Church was targeting him?"

1041.m_mText: "Meanwhile, in a ramshackle house somewhere in the fishing village..."

1042.m_mText: "'You really think I, the great Van Helsing, would lose my way?' Van Helsing muttered to himself as he rummaged through the house."

1043.m_mText: "'The competition is utterly irrelevant! The pearl that the Church seeks is hidden in this very fishing village. That's why I'm really here! And if my guess is correct—'"

1044.m_mText: "Van Helsing violently lifted a wooden plank, revealing a box underneath. 'Come forth, Seafood Tycoon Pearl!' As his words faded, a fierce burst of golden light erupted from the box—!"

2001001.m_mText: "Van Helsing sighed quietly. '...What is it now?' He had made a deal with Goldland before and knew that Goldland was caught up in some trivial matter again."

2002001.m_mText: "'Heh, stalling for time? Already accepting your inevitable defeat?' Cain drawled, his words dripping with sarcasm as he tried to provoke Goldland into revealing everything."

2003001.m_mText: "'...Ah, the Goldland statue is upside down,' Noah's sharp eyes immediately realizing what was truly bothering Goldland."

1.m_mText: "The sea is ever dangerous—yet ever alluring. Even knowing how many lives it's claimed, people still head willingly toward its depths."

1002.m_mText: "'That's a huge misunderstanding. I just wanted to sit quietly and watch the sea.'"

1003.m_mText: "Of course, sometimes a man does just want to watch the sea."

1004.m_mText: "'Give me a moment of peace and quiet.'"

1006.m_mText: "'To sink beneath the sea… it's a wonderful experience.'"

1007.m_mText: "'I swam with the little fish, drifted with the seaweed. My soul felt boundless—until it touched the shore of another.'"

1008.m_mText: "…Wait, when did he get so philosophical?"

1009.m_mText: "If you're so enthralled by the sea, why not just jump in? You won't feel its wonder just standing there."

1010.m_mText: "'The sea isn't all allure. It's not just the pale blue you see from here—the depths are black like tar, thick enough to drown out the loudest screams.'"

1011.m_mText: "Like the color of the sky tonight."

1012.m_mText: "'So do you like the sea, or not?'"

1013.m_mText: "An unexpected voice cut off Noah's communion with the sea."

1015.m_mText: "A sudden force shoved him from behind—followed by a series of splashes and a quiet gurgle."

1016.m_mText: "So much for Noah's hard-earned peace and quiet. Someone had come uninvited. Someone who bore fire, yet willingly approached the sea. Who could it possibly be—"

1017.m_mText: "'My, my. You're looking pretty rough today, Noah.' Agares crouched lazily by the shore, his grin full of mischief."

1018.m_mText: "Still reeling from the sheer audacity, Noah finally spoke. 'You're the one who pushed me in.'"

1019.m_mText: "'Now, now, don't say it like that, Noah. I just gave you a little encouragement.'"

1020.m_mText: "Noah hesitated, then sighed. 'I just wanted to watch the sea, not take a dip in it.'"

1021.m_mText: "'Forget it. What's done is done.' But just as Agares assumed Noah had resigned himself to floating there in quiet defeat—"

1023.m_mText: "'You really don't let things go, do you?'"

1024.m_mText: "'Although I pulled you… why do I get the feeling you deliberately jumped in?'"

1025.m_mText: "Agares let out a rare, hearty laugh. 'I suppose I wanted to experience what it's like to hit the water the same way you did.'"

1026.m_mText: "It's best to keep distance from people who have a few screws loose. Noah made a point by putting some distance between them."

1027.m_mText: "'Still… same dive or not, yours lacked my signature flair.'"

1028.m_mText: "Agares slicked his hair back with a sweep of his hand, then paused, eyes glinting with some fresh mischief."

1029.m_mText: "'Why don't we have a race? See who's the better swimmer.'"

1030.m_mText: "Noah gave him a long, bewildered stare, as if unsure whether he heard Agares correctly."

1032.m_mText: "He rubbed his chin—whatever he'd just thought of, it definitely wasn't anything good."

2002.m_mText: "A rival who's both enemy and friend?"

2001001.m_mText: "Partner? Maybe only a small part of him qualified as that…"

2001002.m_mText: "'Come now, Noah. Surely half of me counts as a partner, at least.'"

2004001.m_mText: "Noah's lips curled into a small smile. 'Fine.'"

2004002.m_mText: "Then Noah suddenly shook his head hard. 'Wait. Did something just take over my body for a second…?'"

2004003.m_mText: "Agares raised an eyebrow. 'I just know you agreed to my terms.'"

2005001.m_mText: "Noah was confused, 'Still don't know where you got that idea…'"

2006001.m_mText: "He kept a straight face, but the irritation was clear in his voice. 'Why would I race the guy who shoved me into the sea?'"

1.m_mText: "A woman with pale golden hair stood before a wooden cabin in the fishing village, her gaze fixed on the distant horizon. The sea breeze stirred her hair, carrying away with it a trace of her melancholy."

1002.m_mText: "'That child... still as playful as ever, I wonder? I hope it won't interfere with her duties... Though perhaps for her, play is what truly matters.'"

1003.m_mText: "Before she could finish her thought, Acappella's voice suddenly rang out from behind her. 'My, my, what gossip is our Commander spreading now?'"

1004.m_mText: "The golden-haired woman seemed unsurprised by Acappella's appearance. 'Ah, you've arrived early. Please, come in, honorable Bell Ringer.'"

1005.m_mText: "'No fun at all! You've always had that same smile, Commander, for as long as I can remember,' Acappella waved her hand dismissively. 'Just once, I'd love to see you caught off guard!'"

1006.m_mText: "The golden-haired woman smiled as she watched Acappella's figure enter the cabin, then turned her gaze back to where the sea met the sky. '...I hope no storm is brewing.'"

1008.m_mText: "'If you keep dragging your feet, I'm leaving without you, you dummy Empousa!'"

1009.m_mText: "'Hey, watch how you talk to your sister! If anyone's a dummy, it's you, Lamia!' Empousa shot back while hastily changing clothes and gathering her things."

1010.m_mText: "'Ugh... why do we have to go to some backwater fishing village...' Empousa muttered under her breath. 'And with Lamia of all people—'"

1011.m_mText: "'What nonsense are you talking about, you dummy Empousa? Nobody's forcing you to come. You're the one who insisted—'"

1012.m_mText: "'Alright, alright! Stop nagging already!' Empousa stormed out of the room and headed for the castle gates. 'Let's go before Cain gives us another lecture.'"

1013.m_mText: "'Tch, look who's dawdling now...' Lamia followed Empousa toward the castle gates. 'But... what's the point of going to that wretched fishing village anyway?'"

1014.m_mText: "A while later, at a sandy area in Cerulean Fishing Village—"

1015.m_mText: "'Ugh... the salty sea air and fishy stench...' Empousa wrinkled her nose, covering it with one hand. 'Could a place like this really have what Cain mentioned—'"

1016.m_mText: "'Shh, be quiet!' Sensing something, Lamia held out an arm to stop Empousa. The sisters quickly ducked into the shadows, staying on high alert."

1017.m_mText: "Moments later, Acappella and the golden-haired woman appeared in the distance, glancing around as if searching for something."

1018.m_mText: "'Should be around here somewhere, Commander.' Acappella casually flipped open a nearby wooden box. 'Though... I wonder what you plan to do with 'that thing' once we find it?'"

1019.m_mText: "The golden-haired woman was about to answer when she suddenly turned toward where Empousa and Lamia were hiding. 'Would our guests care to show themselves?'"

1020.m_mText: "'Going by their aura, they must be from the Bathory family.' The golden-haired woman turned to Acappella. 'Acappella, you sensed it too, didn't you?'"

1021.m_mText: "'As sharp as ever, Commander... And here I thought retirement might have dulled your senses a bit.'"

1022.m_mText: "Lamia stepped out from the shadows. 'Tch, we got caught because you couldn't mask your presence properly, Empousa. Useless dummy!'"

1023.m_mText: "'Huh? I didn't do anything!' Empousa jumped out. 'Don't let her size fool you—she's a genuine Bell Ringer from the Church!'"

1024.m_mText: "'What's the big deal about being discovered by a Bell Ringer?' Empousa excitedly pointed at Acappella across from them. 'You're totally underestimating what a Bell Ringer can do, Lamia!'"

1025.m_mText: "'Hey, who are you calling a weak little runt?' Acappella was visibly getting worked up."

1026.m_mText: "'...Why are you making such a big deal out of this?' Empousa covered her face in exasperation. 'Why do I have to deal with these people...'"

1027.m_mText: "'Now, now, let's not point fingers at each other.' The golden-haired woman clapped her hands to quiet everyone down. 'After all, none of us came here today to fight, did we?'"

1028.m_mText: "Her words brought an immediate silence—she had clearly struck a chord; everyone present obviously had more important matters to attend to."

1029.m_mText: "'And who might you be? You're acting like you know everything... Are you just putting on an act?'"

1030.m_mText: "'Tris, former commander of the Church choir.' Tris gave a slight nod. 'So, young ladies of Bathory, I assume you're also here for 'that thing'?'"

1031.m_mText: "'...Hmph, I'm not wasting my breath on you!' Empousa put her hands on her hips. 'Church choir? You're nothing but the Church's weapons. No matter how you dress it up, enemies are enemies.'"

1032.m_mText: "'The Church isn't quite what you imagine—'"

1033.m_mText: "'Save your excuses!' Lamia violently waved her hand to cut off Tris. 'If it weren't for the Church, the Bathory family wouldn't have...' Her voice trailed off."

1034.m_mText: "'Hahaha, and here I thought you were building up to something profound...' Acappella laughed, clapping her hands. 'Instead it's just the same old mindless drivel. How hilarious!'"

1035.m_mText: "'What could a brat like you possibly know about the Bathory family?' Empousa pointed at Acappella. 'The Church has never shown our families an ounce of respect.'"

1036.m_mText: "As tensions rose between the two sides... Tris suddenly stepped forward, positioning herself between the opposing groups with an outstretched hand."

1037.m_mText: "'Surely we didn't all come here just to trade words?' Tris smiled as she swept her gaze across everyone present. 'Why don't we settle this with a proper contest? Let our abilities do the talking.'"

1038.m_mText: "'A contest...?' Lamia crossed her arms, eyeing Tris suspiciously. 'You're not planning to use this as a cover for something else, are you?'"

1039.m_mText: "'As if I'd bother with such complicated schemes.' Acappella shot Lamia a contemptuous glance. 'See, Commander? I told you they wouldn't appreciate it.'"

1040.m_mText: "'Appreciate it?' Empousa's brow furrowed. 'The Bathory family needs no charity from the Church!'"

1041.m_mText: "'The Bathory family and the Church are allies, at least on the surface...' Tris calmly explained the situation to Empousa. 'You wouldn't want to destroy that facade, would you?'"

1044.m_mText: "'Tch, so what's this contest you're proposing?' Lamia flipped her hair back and took a step forward, looking down at Tris with disdain."

1045.m_mText: "Tris glanced around the area. 'Since we're in a fishing village... how about a fishing contest?'"

1046.m_mText: "'Hmph, is this really the best that the Church's weapon and Bell Ringer can come up with?' Empousa shook her head lightly, mocking Tris's suggestion."

1047.m_mText: "Fishing does sound a bit dull, even if it was Commander's idea...' Acappella tilted her head in thought. 'Ah! I know—let's play ball!'"

2001001.m_mText: "...Ah, it seems to be the case. Like we've seen (or will see) similar stories before (or in the future). Perhaps we should try something else."
